ATHLETES OF THE WEEK APRIL 23-29
Athletes of the Week: Oak Hills' Jordan Dominguez and University Prep's Justice Borden
Comment
VVdailypress.com
Writer
Posted May. 2, 2016 at 8:26 PM
Updated at 8:32 PM
Posted May. 2, 2016 at 8:26 PM
Updated at 8:32 PM
Social News
Name: Jordan Dominguez Sport: Prep Boys Tennis School: Oak Hills Grade: Senior This weeks accomplishment: Dominguez won eight of the nine sets he played to help the Bulldogs clinch the Mojave River League title. He lost just four games in the eight sets he won. What do you like most about your sport: I love everything about tennis. Winning, losing, the competition and the emotions it brings me. I believe it teaches me about life. How long have you been playing your sport and how did you get started: I have been playing for three complete years. I played tennis because I didnt want to do track and field, and I had to play a sport. Pregame ritual: Before a match I regrip my racquets, put my ankle braces on, prepare my water and get my Rafa towel. The most important is I put on my headbands and wristbands. Most memorable sports moment: Winning both the Hesperia and King of the Desert tournaments this year. If you could be someone else for a day, who would it be and why: I would pick my favorite tennis player Rafael Nadal because he is one of the best players ever. Something most people dont know about you: I like to talk, and I am really weird. How would you spend $1 million: I would spend it on tennis gear, and I would make myself a tennis court. Where would you go if you could travel anywhere in the world: I would go to Japan. If you had an extra hour every day, how would you spend it: I would spend it playing tennis. What superpower do you wish you had: To go back in time. Favorite sports team: Baseball it is the Angels. Football it is the New Orleans Saints. Favorite athlete: Rafael Nadal Favorite superhero: Green Lantern Favorite TV show: Daredevil Favorite movie: Batman v. Superman: Dawn of Justice Favorite song: Live on Forever by the Afters Favorite meal: Lasagna Favorite local restaurant: BJs Restaurant and Brewhouse Favorite app: Instagram Twitter handle: @sasuketiger
Name: Justice Borden Sport: Prep Softball School: University Prep Grade: Senior This weeks accomplishment: Borden hit a home run and drove in three runs in a win over Excelsior, then went 3 for 4 with two home runs, three RBIs and three runs in a win against Riverside Prep. What do you like most about your sport: I love the intensity and the fact that you have to be ready at any moment. How long have you been playing your sport and how did you get started: Ive been playing for seven years and my parents made me play Little League because my dad played baseball. Pregame ritual: I write my uncles initials in the dirt by my position in memory of him. Most memorable sports moment: My grand slam off Chloe Romero to put our team on top in my junior year against ACE. If you could be someone else for a day, who would it be and why: Myself because I would never want to be someone else. Something most people dont know about you: Im really shy and a little anti-social. How would you spend $1 million: I would put it in a mutual fund and later become a billionaire. Where would you go if you could travel anywhere in the world: I would go to Europe. If you had an extra hour every day, how would you spend it: I would spend the extra hour studying. What superpower do you wish you had: Teleportation. Favorite sports team: New York Yankees Favorite athlete: Ms. Thomas (my softball coach at University Prep) Favorite superhero: Superman Favorite TV show: Chicago Med Favorite movie: The Proposal Favorite song: Work by Rihanna Favorite meal: Cheese enchiladas Favorite local restaurant: Yoshi Sushi Favorite app: Snapchat Twitter handle: @justacio_
For more sports talk, visit http://910cbssports.cbslocal.com.
